  "prompt": "Which countries have never been conquered, colonized, or ruled by any other country?",
  "response": "While the nuances of history make it difficult to claim that any country has been completely free from foreign influence or control, there are a few nations often cited as having avoided colonization or conquest in the traditional sense. Here are some examples:\n\n1. **Japan**: Though Japan experienced significant foreign influence, particularly in the late 19th and early 20th centuries, it was never colonized. Notably, Japan was an imperial power itself, engaging in colonization in Asia.\n\n2. **Thailand**: Thailand (formerly Siam) is notable for having avoided European colonization. It skillfully navigated complex political landscapes and made strategic concessions to maintain its sovereignty.\n\n3. **Liberia**: Founded by freed American slaves under the auspices of the American Colonization Society, Liberia maintained its independence during the European \"Scramble for Africa,\" though its creation was directly influenced by external forces.\n\n4. **Ethiopia**: Ethiopia successfully resisted colonization by European powers, famously defeating Italy at the Battle of Adwa in 1896. However, it was briefly occupied by Italy from 1936 to 1941 during World War II.\n\nIt is important to note that the concept of being \"never conquered, colonized, or ruled\" is complex, as many nations have experienced various degrees of foreign influence, intervention, or control at different points in their histories.",
